            "creation_date": 1372866289,
            "body": "<p>Read the <code>JOptionPane API<\/code>. It shows you how to create a JOption pane manually so that you have access to the JDialog. Once you have the JDialog you can remove the Border the same way you did in your last question: <\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/q/17413658/131872\">Undecorated JDialog border<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 17452427,
            "question_id": 17452235,
            "last_edit_date": 1495540702
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-yCayz6eZxuk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABE/Zha2FvJeJtk/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 7005761,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5370194,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5370194/jun",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "Jun"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1443061606,
            "creation_date": 1443061606,
            "body": "<p>I have research on it these days, finally I found this code may help you!<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>UIManager.put(\"RootPane.frameBorder\", new LineBorder(Color.red));\nUIManager.put(\"RootPane.dialogBorder\", new LineBorder(Color.red));    \nUIManager.put(\"RootPane.errorDialogBorder\", new LineBorder(Color.red));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 32752359,
            "question_id": 17452235
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/2084481638263811/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 14474561,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 10455534,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10455534/tamara-koliada",
                "reputation": 1204,
                "display_name": "Tamara Koliada"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1546530548,
            "creation_date": 1546530548,
            "body": "<p>In LaF section there is the initialization of <code>ShadowPopupBorder<\/code> which used for tooltips, popups, and modal dialogs borders. So check if it is used around your software<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 54025592,
            "question_id": 17452235
        }
